regions.title: Vertical crack and discoloration near wall corner
regions.description: This region contains a vertical area along the corner of the wall, displaying visible signs of structural damage such as cracks, discoloration, and possible water intrusion. The affected area extends from mid-height to the base, and includes the intersection of two wall planes, which may indicate weakness or ongoing deterioration.

summary: A single, connected region of structural concern is present along the corner of the wall, evidenced by cracking, discoloration, and signs of possible water damage. The high vote counts and contiguous pattern suggest a credible structural issue in this area. No extraneous or low-confidence detections were present.
